### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

# 1. First, Create a Media Asset and copy the ID from the response
# 2. Paste that ID here:
@mediaId = REPLACE_WITH_UUID_FROM_MEDIA_POST_RESPONSE

# 3. Use this slug for testing
@projectSlug = my-pro-portfolio-2026

// ==========================================
// 1. MEDIA ASSETS (Run this first!)
// ==========================================

### üñºÔ∏è Create Media Asset
# This provides the ID needed for the project thumbnail
POST {{baseUrl}}/media
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fileName": "Ai-thumbnail.png",
  "fileUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551288049-bebda4e38f71?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200",
  "fileType": "image/png",
  "fileSize": 102400
}


### üìÇ Get All Media Assets
GET {{baseUrl}}/media
Content-Type: application/json


// ==========================================
// 2. PROJECT SYSTEM
// ==========================================

### ‚úçÔ∏è Create New Project
# IMPORTANT: Use the @mediaId generated above. 
# If you don't have an ID yet, set "mainThumbnailId" to null.
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Professional Portfolio 2026",
  "slug": "{{projectSlug}}",
  "mainDescription": "An elite portfolio built with Drizzle ORM and UUIDs.",
  "mainThumbnailId": "{{mediaId}}",
  "status": "published",
  "isFeatured": true
}


### ‚úÖ Get All Projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects
Content-Type: application/json


### üîó Get Project By Slug
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/slug/{{projectSlug}}
Content-Type: application/json


### üÜî Get Project By ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{mediaId}}
Content-Type: application/json


// ==========================================
// 3. CLEANUP
// ==========================================

### ‚ùå Delete Media Asset
# Note: This will fail if a project is currently using this ID!
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/media/{{mediaId}}
Content-Type: application/json


### ‚ùå Delete Project
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{mediaId}}
Content-Type: application/json